Explanation:

We use the Arrays.sort() method in Java to sort the names array based on the heights array. The compareTo() method of the Integer class is used to compare two heights, and the lambda expression is used to pass the comparison function to Arrays.sort(). The resulting sorted names array is then returned. The time complexity is O(n log n) due to the sorting operation, and the space complexity is O(1) as we only use a constant amount of space for the lambda expression and the sorted array. The energy implications are low as the solution only involves simple array operations and does not require any complex algorithms or data structures.

